commitmsg: Note that this project is obsolete.

Ensure that 'yarn run watch' works with hard links

This makes it possible for 'yarn run watch' to correctly detect file changes when a Fathom project's source 'trainees.js' is hardlinked to fathom-trainees' target 'trainees.js', even if that source 'trainees.js' has 'import' statements. Any changes to the imported files will also be correctly detected as a file change.

See https://github.com/mozilla/fathom-trainees/issues/8#issuecomment-541253062 for more information.
Updates required version of fathom-web to 3.1

Add Mozilla Code of Conduct file

Fixes #5.

_(Message COC002)_
Remove a comment that came to nothing.
Note that ruleset() takes an array of rules now.
Update the comments.
Add version history to readme.
Bump Fathom dependency to >=3.0a1<4.0.

Remove ONEISH and ZEROISH in favor of hard 1s and 0s.

This doesn't seem to affect the convergence rate of the loss function during training: the initial random weights have a greater effect.
Add vectorType declaration.
Port to mappish coefficients, named rules, and internal weighting.
Update to Fathom 2.8, which lets us click Bad cells to see what element was wrongly selected.

Add hashes for dependencies.

I'm sad some of them are SHA1s. We should figure out why at some point.
Document the newly available pluggable success functions. Depend on a newer Fathom that provides them.
Remove generated code that should have been gone in a35774c2067e7d16853052910e184d2c75004b5b.
Factor out boilerplate into Fathom itself. Fix #1.

Make viewport size configurable per trainee.

Obsolete `traineeCoeffs` message in favor of `trainee` so we don't need new logic for each new property.

This will require FathomFox 1.4 or higher.

Rename the command for installing dependencies, avoiding an infinite `yarn` loop.

It turns out `install` is short for `postinstall`, which npm and yarn call after installing. See https://github.com/yarnpkg/yarn/issues/2335.
Use the now-released Fathom 2.4, getting rid of the git submodule which pointed to a prerelease branch.

Add a `yarn run install` script that works around a bad engine constraint in a deep dependency.

This solves `error mutable-proxy@0.1.7: The engine "node" is incompatible with this module. Expected version "6.X.X".`.
Describe the overlay ruleset.
Add the missing "yarn install" step.
Make intro a bit clearer.
Add readme and `yarn run browser`.
Polish extension ID and description, and remove unneeded permissions.
Improve trainees doclet.
Rename "trainables" to the existing word "trainees".

Add Fathom as a submodule.

We use the branch that I've ported to use ES2015-style imports, so rollup is happy.

Restore the original synchronous approach. All external messages work now.

Turns out I was editing the wrong file when it wasn't working.
Get external messaging working via async.
The external-message handler fires, but the sender just gets an empty object as a reply.
